=Status=

Eleftherios Kosmas:

"Its successful delivery to Innovative Solutions In Space (ISISpace) took place on August 18th in Delft, Netherlands. UPSat is the first complete delivery to ISISpace as part of the QB50 project. ... UPSat will be delivered to Orbital ATK, and then launched to the International Space Station via a Cygnus automated cargo spacecraft. After successful docking to ISS, UPSat will be launch by the NanoRacks deployment pod aboard ISS."
(https://upsat.gr/?p=344)

